6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to contracts; requiring vendors of
goods and services to disclose price and related cost
8 information; requiring disclosure of state and local
sales tax amounts; providing for statement of
9 shipping costs; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1101 of Title 15, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Any vendor of goods or services shall clearly identify the
17 actual price to be paid by the buyer for the goods or services which
18 shall include any fees, charges, or other costs to be paid by the
19 buyer.
20 B. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall also
21 apply to the total amount of state and local sales tax, if
22 applicable.
23
